# SEAFARER APP — Enterprise Cursor Rules
Telegram Mini App (TMA) Job Platform for Seafarers

Stack:
- FastAPI (async)
- Aiogram 3.x
- PostgreSQL
- SQLAlchemy 2.0 (AsyncSession)
- Alembic
- Pydantic v2
- pydantic-settings
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- Tailwind CSS
- @twa-dev/sdk
- SWR or TanStack Query

====================================================
1. SECURITY — ZERO TRUST POLICY
====================================================

1.1 Telegram initData — Mandatory

- NO endpoint without initData validation (except /health).
- HMAC-SHA256 using BOT_TOKEN.
- Validate auth_date: reject if older than INIT_DATA_MAX_AGE_MINUTES.
- Implement as global FastAPI dependency.
- Attach validated user to request context.
- Never log raw initData.
- Never expose Telegram payload in response.

1.2 Rate Limiting

- Rate limit by Telegram user_id.
- Protect:
  - Job search
  - Job apply
  - Auth endpoints
- Use middleware or dependency.
- Prevent brute-force or scraping behavior.

1.3 Logging Policy

- Structured logging only (JSON in production).
- Log:
  - user_id
  - endpoint
  - status_code
  - execution_time
- DO NOT log:
  - initData
  - tokens
  - raw request bodies
  - DB credentials

1.4 CORS

- Restrict allowed origins.
- No wildcard in production.

====================================================
2. ASYNC-ONLY BACKEND POLICY
====================================================

- All endpoints: async def
- All bot handlers: async def
- All DB access: AsyncSession
- No blocking calls.
- No sync SQLAlchemy.

====================================================
3. PROJECT STRUCTURE
====================================================

Required layout:

/backend/app/models/
/backend/app/schemas/
/backend/app/services/
/backend/app/api/
/backend/app/bot/
/backend/app/core/ (settings, security, rate limit)

Rules:

- Shared models between bot and API.
- Shared schemas between bot and API.
- Business logic only in services.
- Routers and handlers are thin.

====================================================
4. CONFIGURATION (Pydantic Settings ONLY)
====================================================

4.1 Backend (Python)

- Use pydantic-settings with BaseSettings.
- Create a typed Settings class in app/core/settings.py.
- Single source of truth. No os.getenv() in application code.
- Load from .env (dotenv). Env file: .env.example as template.
- Support ENVIRONMENT=development|staging|production.
- BOT_TOKEN, DATABASE_URL, SECRET_KEY must come from Settings.
- Optional fields: use default values or Optional[].
- Validation: use model_validator for cross-field checks.

4.2 Settings class pattern

  from pydantic_settings import BaseSettings
  class Settings(BaseSettings):
      model_config = SettingsConfigDict(env_file=".env", extra="ignore")
      BOT_TOKEN: str
      DATABASE_URL: str
      ENVIRONMENT: str = "development"
      RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS: int = 100
      PAGINATION_MAX_LIMIT: int = 50
      # ...

4.3 Required env vars (backend)

  - BOT_TOKEN
  - DATABASE_URL
  - SECRET_KEY
  - ALLOWED_ORIGINS (when ENABLE_CORS=true)

4.4 Frontend (Next.js)

- Use frontend/.env.local for local overrides.
- NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars are exposed to client (e.g. NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL).
- Template: frontend/.env.example.
- Never put secrets in NEXT_PUBLIC_*.

====================================================
5. DATABASE STANDARDS
====================================================

5.1 SQLAlchemy 2.0 Strict

- select(Model).where(...)
- await session.execute(...)
- async with session.begin()

5.2 Base Model Requirements

Every table MUST include:

- id (PK)
- created_at (timezone aware)
- updated_at (timezone aware)
- is_deleted (boolean, default False)

5.3 Soft Delete Policy

- NEVER hard-delete records.
- Use `is_deleted = True`.
- All queries must exclude deleted rows unless explicitly requested.

5.4 Indexing Policy

Jobs table must have indexes on:

- rank
- vessel_type
- salary
- joining_date
- created_at

Use pg_trgm for:
- title
- company_name
- vessel_type

5.5 Migrations

After ANY model change:

1. Generate Alembic migration.
2. Review diff.
3. Apply to dev DB.
4. Mention in commit notes.

====================================================
6. Pydantic v2 Strict Policy
====================================================

- No raw ORM return.
- All responses use response_model.
- Validation must happen via schemas.
- Separate:
  - CreateDTO
  - UpdateDTO
  - ResponseDTO

====================================================
7. MARITIME DOMAIN RULES
====================================================

Job MUST include:

- rank (canonical)
- vessel_type
- dwt or grt
- engine_type
- salary
- contract_months

Recommended:

- joining_date
- company_id
- company_name
- verified_company
- english_level
- nationality_restrictions
- visa_requirements
- internet_onboard

====================================================
8. RANK NORMALIZATION
====================================================

- Normalize input rank before DB filtering.
- Map aliases:
  - 2O
  - 2/O
  - OOW
  → second_officer

- Store canonical rank in DB.
- Fuzzy search only as fallback.

====================================================
9. SEARCH ENGINEERING
====================================================

- Always server-side pagination.
- Max limit per page: use PAGINATION_MAX_LIMIT from config (default 50).
- Enforce in service/repository layer.
- Use optimized indexes.
- No unbounded queries allowed.

====================================================
10. ROLE-BASED ACCESS CONTROL (RBAC)
====================================================

Roles:

- seafarer
- company_admin
- super_admin

Rules:

- Seafarer:
  - Can view jobs
  - Can apply to jobs
  - Cannot create/edit jobs

- Company_admin:
  - Can create/edit own jobs
  - Cannot edit other companies' jobs

- Super_admin:
  - Full access

Role must be derived from DB user model (not from frontend input).

====================================================
11. ERROR HANDLING STANDARD
====================================================

API errors MUST:

- Return consistent format:
  { "detail": "Human-readable message" }

- Never expose stack traces.
- Never expose internal implementation.

Frontend MUST:

- Use centralized API error handler.
- Display readable message.
- Trigger:
  WebApp.HapticFeedback.notificationOccurred("error")

====================================================
12. FRONTEND (TMA STRICT MODE)
====================================================

12.1 Integration

- Always call WebApp.ready().
- Use Telegram theme variables.
- Use WebApp.MainButton for primary action.

12.2 UX

- Use HapticFeedback for:
  - Apply
  - Save
  - Critical confirmation
- Handle BackButton properly.
- Sync navigation with Next router.

12.3 Data Layer

- Use SWR or TanStack Query.
- No manual fetch logic duplication.
- Centralized API client.

====================================================
13. PROHIBITIONS
====================================================

- No .env in git (use .env.example as template only).
- No jQuery.
- No legacy JS.
- No endpoints without initData validation.
- No os.getenv().
- No hard deletes.
- No raw SQL without necessity.
- No sensitive data in logs.
- No direct DB exposure.
- No fat routers or handlers.

====================================================
14. PERFORMANCE & PRODUCTION READINESS
====================================================

- Use connection pooling.
- Use DB indexes for frequent filters.
- Enforce max pagination size.
- Log slow queries.
- Prepare for horizontal scaling (stateless API).

====================================================
15. GIT & COMMITS
====================================================

- Never commit .env (only .env.example).
- Commit message format: conventional (feat, fix, docs, chore).
- Keep commits atomic and focused.
- Migrations: always review alembic diff before commit.

====================================================
16. FILE NAMING
====================================================

Backend (Python):
- Modules: snake_case (user_service.py, job_schemas.py).
- Classes: PascalCase.

Frontend (TypeScript/React):
- Components: PascalCase (JobCard.tsx).
- Hooks: camelCase with use prefix (useJobs.ts).
- Utils/lib: camelCase or kebab-case.

====================================================
17. EDITOR & FORMATTING
====================================================

- Follow .editorconfig (Python: 4 spaces, JS/TS: 2 spaces).
- Python: use ruff or black for formatting.
- Trim trailing whitespace, insert final newline.
- Charset: UTF-8. Line endings: LF.

====================================================
18. INFRA
====================================================

- Use docker-compose.yml for local PostgreSQL.
- Use Makefile for common dev commands (make api, make migrate, make migrate-create).
- .gitignore: .env, __pycache__, node_modules, .next, .mypy_cache, .ruff_cache.
- See docs/infra.md for full infra reference.

====================================================
END OF ENTERPRISE RULESET
====================================================